SIMPLE: biotin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: biotin
<hw>bi"o*tin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a B vitamin
(<chform>C10H16N2O3S</chform>) that aids in body growth; -- called also
<altname>vitamin H</altname> and <altname>coenzyme R</altname>. It
functions as a coenzyme in many carboxylation reactions.</def>
<note>Biotin binds tightly to the substance avidin, found in raw
egg-whites. Rats or chick on a diet high in raw egg-white may develop
skin lesions and retarded growth, which can be prevented by adding
biotin to the diet.</note> <au>[MI11]</au>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> .</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

